<subSubSection id="65A7652EC07C4B1EFF014C48FEC0354D" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C07C4B1EFF014C48FEC0354D" blockId="29.[192,1440,285,346]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFF014C48FE8B3520" bold="true" box="[192,316,285,311]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The floricolorous marking on the elytron disc (
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C07C4B1EFC8F4C48FC1D352F" box="[846,938,285,312]" captionStart="Figures 102–105" captionStartId="66.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-11@66.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="Figures 102–105. Habitus of Axina species. 102) Axina pallidioccabus. 103) A. picta. 104) A. piperata. 105) A. pollex." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565027" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565027/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) will distinguish the members of this species from congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A7652EC07C4B1EFF014C3FFCD2368F" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph id="2D0236A5C07C4B1EFF014C3FFCD2368F" blockId="29.[191,1442,362,664]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFF014C3FFED33593" bold="true" box="[192,356,362,388]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Redescription</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFEB04C3EFE2B3592" box="[369,412,363,389]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Size</emphasis>
. Length 12.0 mm; width 3.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFCDB4C3EFCE23593" box="[794,853,363,388]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Form</emphasis>
. As in 
<figureCitation id="B5862A20C07C4B1EFC654C3FFBB73593" box="[932,1024,362,388]" captionStart="Figures 102–105" captionStartId="66.[192,279,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-11@66.[192,1440,213,1828]" captionTargetPageId="66" captionText="Figures 102–105. Habitus of Axina species. 102) Axina pallidioccabus. 103) A. picta. 104) A. piperata. 105) A. pollex." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565027" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4565027/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFBCB4C3FFBF03593" box="[1034,1095,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Color</emphasis>
. Cranium castaneous; antenna testaceous; prothorax bicolorous, venter flavotestaceous; pronotal sides and pronotal arch black, pronotum middle widely testaceous, testaceous area flows into subapical depression; pterothorax light castaneous; elytra bicolorous, X-like testaceous making that extends along sutural margin to elytral anterior margin, remainder of elytra dark brown, except elytral apical ¼ testaceous; legs dark mostly dark brown castaneous, except basal region of femora testaceous; abdomen testaceous. Head. Cranium finely punctate, frons about as wide as length of antennal pedicel; EW/FW 65/11. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFD984F6CFD113644" box="[601,678,569,595]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Thorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum finely punctate, with 2 tumescences, concave at middle; PW/PL 130/170; elytra, asetiferous punctures not striate, punctures extend to elytral apical 3/4, interstitial spaces very wide; EL/EW 490/110. 
<emphasis id="1FC9EAB7C07C4B1EFE384F2BFDD4368F" box="[505,611,638,664]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Pygidium securiform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
